Swedish electro producer, Ola Bergman (aka https://soundcloud.com/obergman) first appeared on my musical radar a few years back when I heard his ‘Quantum Eraser EP’ on Brokntoys. It blew me away. I’ve been pretty much buying all his records since and playing his tracks in my mixes. A few that cost a pretty penny on Discogs, I may add!

In more recent years, he has moved towards 4/4, although not exclusively, and has carved out a niche for his unique electro-tinged robo-house. I was hooked with this style that has this amazing hypnotic, deep, wonky feel to it, while still sounding futuristic and in the electro realm.

His impressive discography includes releases on labels such as Infiltrate, Pariter, Brokntoys, Stilleben, Furthur Electronix, Börft, Propaganda, Between Places and most recently Craigie Knowes.

Obergman has prepared an hour-long live set for us that is class from start to finish.

track.description:
Para la entrega número 52 de la serie de mixes tenemos el placer de presentarles a Domingo Dark Vinyl aka @Kaxtelian.

Trepidantes, frenéticas y emocionantes son las cualidades principales de cualquier sesión de Domingo Dark Vinyl Aka Kaxtelian, mezclador, locutor y productor que lleva girando los platos desde 1994. Siempre en la vanguardia de nuevos ritmos y sonidos apuesta por el eclecticismo en sus sesiones, siempre a tres o cuatro platos, sirviendo un energético y dinámico menú que se pasea entre el Chicago Techno, Electro, EBM, GhettoTech, Goa Trance, Detroit  Techno, UK Breaks, Italo, Footwork, Gabber o cualquier otro género con tal de sorprender en la pista. Su maleta ha surcado gran parte de la geografía española llevándole a pinchar en clubs tan míticos como: Specka, Camelot, Spook Factory o Metro Dance Club entre otros. Actualmente pertenece al equipo del sello HC Records donde está a punto de publicar su primer vinilo en solitario titulado Ghetto Bangers.
